haas center for public service jumpstart student affairs haas center for public service students faculty alumni community about stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit jumpstart jumpstart background and purpose student involvement application jumpstart haas center for public service program students jumpstart east palo alto pairs stanford students with preschool children in east palo alto childcare centers to deliver an innovative early learning program jumpstart provides a high quality comprehensive curriculum that focuses on the development of the child his or her family and the university student serving with this national organization as an americorps member through these program areas school success family involvement and future teachers jumpstart works to create an environment of lifelong learning for under resourced children the jumpstart east palo alto program is made up of highly trained motivated and passionate university students who are paired with preschool children in caring and supportive one to one relationships after satisfying coursework requirements as outlined by the school of education which focus on early childhood education and offer the training support reflection and context necessary for success in the preschool stanford students mentor 3 to 5 year old children in preschool classes at the ravenswood child development center in east palo alto students read stories sing songs and play games that support young children's school readiness be a part of read for the record day join jumpstart's annual read for the record day on thursday october 6 and help call for an end to the early education achievement gap the goal of this event is to get every child in the us to read the same book on the same day last year over 2 milliion children participated this year's book is anna dewdney's llama llama red pajama every child receives the book in english or spanish to take home as a volunteer you receive a copy too if you are interested in participating email elizabeth figueredo a van will leave the haas center on october 6 at 8 30 am and return no later than 10 30 am for more information about jumpstart please contact elizabeth figueredo background and purpose student involvement application background and purpose groups haas center for public service printer friendly version education & youth programs at haas east palo alto stanford acadamy jumpstart stanford college prep science in service ravenswood reads connect with us facebook facebook twitter twitter video icon video stanford seal newsletter giving to haas action logo support our work haas center for public service 562 salvatierra walk stanford ca 94305 650 723 0992 hours m f 8 5 support our work feedback copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
